FBIS3-429 "drafr045_d_94001" FBIS-AFR-94-045 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Mar 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Angola UNITA: Portuguese Soldiers Fighting for Government LD0703151594 Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network in Portuguese 1400 GMT 7 Mar 94 LD0703151594 Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] UNITA [National Union for the Total Independence of Angola] has repeated its accusation that there are Portuguese soldiers fighting for the Angolan government forces. The accusation comes this time from UNITA in northern Angola. General Abilio Kamalata Numa said that Portuguese marines and Zairean soldiers are participating in clashes taking place in northern Angola, namely in the Uige and Zaire Provinces.
